<h1>Rule of 72 Calculator</h1>
<img class="img-fluid rounded" src="images/site/72.png" height="200" width="200" alt="rule72 ">
<p>The Rule of 72 is a simple formula used to estimate the number of years it will take to double your investment at a given interest rate. To use the rule, simply divide 72 by the interest rate. For example, if the interest rate is 6%, it would take approximately 12 years to double your investment (72 / 6 = 12).</p>
<p class="formula">Years to Double = 72 / Interest Rate</p>
<form>
    <label for="interest-rate">Interest Rate:</label>
    <input type="number" id="interest-rate" name="interest-rate" value="2" step="0.01">
    <br><br>
    <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" onclick="calculate()">Calculate</button>
</form>
